public class FlexfieldRevisionKey
extends java.lang.Object

ApplCore Internal Use Only. Applications should not use this class.

A key to flexfield business component model revision information.

Gets the package of the revision information files. Each flexfield has its own package.

Parameters:

Returns:

updateRevisionInfo

public static final void updateRevisionInfo(java.lang.String flexfieldType,
                                            java.lang.String applicationId,
                                            java.lang.String flexfieldCode,
                                            java.lang.String version)
Updates the revision information file for a flexfield. The file will contain a new revision ID after this method is completed successfully.

Parameters:
flexfieldType - the flexfield type, which is "DFF", "EFF" or "KFF"
applicationId - the appliation ID
flexfieldCode - the flexfield code
version - a version number if applicable; null if not available
Throws:
java.lang.NullPointerException - if any of the arguments is null

versionExists

public static final boolean versionExists(java.lang.String flexfieldType,
                                          java.lang.String applicationId,
                                          java.lang.String flexfieldCode)
Returns true if the version information exists for a flexfield.

Parameters:
flexfieldType - the flexfield type, which is "DFF", "EFF" or "KFF"
applicationId - the application ID
flexfieldCode - the flexfield code
Returns:
true if the version information exists for the given flexfield; false if the version information does not exists or is not accessible
Throws:
oracle.jbo.JboException - if an error occurs while accessing the version information file
